content: That's a great overview of Judy Chicago's work and significance. I've always been fascinated by The Dinner Party, and I appreciate how it's become an iconic symbol of feminist art. Speaking of feminist art, I just came back from a lecture series at the Museum of Contemporary Art, where Dr. Maria Rodriguez spoke about the role of feminist art in the 1970s, and I enjoyed networking with other art enthusiasts during the reception that followed. It was really enlightening to learn about the historical context of feminist art and its continued relevance today.
